name: maize chop to generic market for energy feed | energy feed, gross | Cutoff, U
description:
ecoQuery: https://ecoquery.ecoinvent.org/3.10/cutoff/dataset/19541/documentation

This activity is a linking activity, i.e. it connects maize chop with generic protein feed market. Maize chop is used partially as a feed for animals, thus traded on generic feed market with other protein - containing products.

The activity starts with the reception of maize chop.

This linking activity has the maize chop as an input (negative reference product) and protein and energy feed as outputs.
category: C:Manufacturing/10:Manufacture of food products/108:Manufacture of prepared animal feeds/1080:Manufacture of prepared animal feeds

processDocumentation.technologyDescription: The data are intended to reflect current equipment and processes on a Global level.

exchanges.description: Calculated based on literature value for "hominy feed" (Feedipedia, 2015), which reports a crude protein content of 15.2% of dry matter; while gross energy content equates to 18.7 MJ/kg dry matter of fed. Dry matter content equates 89.3% of fed. Reference(s): Feedipedia (2015) Hominy Feed, Animal Feed Resources Information System, Available at: https://www.feedipedia.org/node/12290 (Accessed November 2017).
